OL,3,CPeter Mandelson: Can peerages be
OL,4,Crevoked?
OL,6,FA peerage is a form of honour
OL,7,Fappointed by the Crown, following
OL,8,Fadvice of the prime minister,
OL,9,Faccording to the House of Lords
OL,10,FLibrary.
OL,12,FIt acts as a title and a constituent
OL,13,Fpart of the UK honours system, with
OL,14,Frecipients typically entitled to sit
OL,15,Fin the House of Lords.
OL,17,FA peerage can be hereditary, in which
OL,18,Fit is passed down to an heir, usually
OL,19,Fa son. Or, it can be a lifetime
OL,20,Fpeerage, where it lasts the member's
OL,21,Flifetime and cannot be passed on.
