OL,3,CPeter Mandelson: Can peerages be
OL,4,Crevoked?
OL,6,FSeveral acts have previously been
OL,7,Fintroduced to cancel or suspend House
OL,8,Fof Lords memberships in specific
OL,9,Fcircumstances.
OL,11,FFor example, under the House of Lords
OL,12,FReform Act 2014, a person can have
OL,13,Ftheir membership disqualified if they
OL,14,Fhave been sentenced to a year or more
OL,15,Fin prison for a "serious offence", or
OL,16,Ffor at least six months of non-
OL,17,Fattendance in the Lords.
