OL,6,FWhile they will be unable to attend
OL,7,Fthe House or receive a writ of summons
OL,8,F(a document calling Lords to
OL,9,FParliament), their title remains.
OL,11,FThe House of Lords code of conduct
OL,12,Falso states that "a member sentenced
OL,13,Fto imprisonment in the United Kingdom,
OL,14,Fwhether the sentence is suspended or
OL,15,Fnot, shall be deemed to have breached
OL,16,Fthe Code."
